{
  "doc_id": "55466",
  "text": "This study utilized SEER data on patients who were diagnosed with LSBC in the following eight states that comprise 26 % of the US population: California, Georgia, Iowa, Louisiana, Kentucky, New Jersey, New Mexico, and Utah. Cases of LSBC were defined as female, age 40 years or older, diagnosed with LSBC between 2006 and 2010. Late stage was defined as stage III and stage IV, using the guidelines from AJCC (American Joint Commission on Cancer) 6th Edition Cancer Staging Handbook [CITATION_1] .",
